## 🔹 1. Introduction

Geospatial analysis involves analyzing data that has a geographical or location-based component such as latitude and longitude. It helps in visualizing and identifying patterns across different locations.

In the RoadSafe Analytics project, geospatial analysis is used to identify accident-prone areas and understand how location influences accident frequency and severity.

